name: upolicycraft
description: Stateful system call specialization for microservices

name: Hr-employee-and-leave-management-system-microservices
description: A microservices-based solution designed for corporate environments to manage employee profiles, track leave requests, and send notifications. The system includes features like employee management, leave processing, and notifications, leveraging technologies such as Spring Boot, Kafka, MySQL, and Quartz Scheduler for optimal performance.

name: synapsis-library-management-server
description: Library Management System using microservices architecture

name: MS-SpringCloud
description: System created for practicing development with microservices.

name: ecommerce
description: Microservices-based e-commerce system with GraphQL API and event-driven architecture.

name: PaymentProcessingSystem
description: A Payment Processing System using microservices architecture with ASP.NET Core Web API, RabbitMQ (or Kafka), and Docker. This project demonstrates a distributed system handling payment processing, order management, and notifications across three autonomous services, each scalable and capable of independent operation.

name: sritel-web-portal
description: SriTel is a cutting-edge telecommunication solution offering a web portal and mobile apps for account management, service activation, bill payment, and notifications. Built with a microservices architecture using Spring Boot, it integrates with external systems via RESTful APIs.

name: Inno_Shop
description: The Inno_Shop project is a system consisting of two microservices designed to manage users and their products. These microservices are developed using ASP.NET Core and interact via API.

name: catalog_service
description: Catalog Service - A microservice for managing categories, menu items, prices, and modifiers in a multi-restaurant, multi-country system. This service enables seamless CRUD operations and retrieval of menu data with localization support for multiple restaurants and countries.

name: Hospital_management_sys
description: The project is designed to manage hospital operations in a modular, scalable, and maintainable way by separating core functionalities into dedicated microservices. The system includes services for managing patients, doctors, and appointments, each with its own data model and business logic.

name: order_service
description: Order Service - A microservice responsible for managing customer orders, statuses, and associated details within a multi-restaurant, multi-country architecture. Part of a broader order management system, this service handles order creation, tracking, and modification, supporting localized configurations for different restaurants and regions.
